author: Ariel Cohen
title: Webb drops out, considers independent run
text:
Former Sen. Jim Webb announced Tuesday he was withdrawing from the 2016 White House race, but said he was considering other options, a hint he may try again as an Independent.
"I'm stepping aside from the Democratic primary process," he said.
He said he would take a few weeks to talk to people as he decides how to proceed next.
